Just to test, I've replaced the current implementation of [`GraphiteEmitter.sanitize()`](https://github.com/druid-io/druid/blob/master/extensions-contrib/graphite-emitter/src/main/java/io/druid/emitter/graphite/GraphiteEmitter.java#L218) with the following:

``` java
protected static String sanitize(String namespace)
{
    Pattern DOT_OR_WHITESPACE_OR_COLON = Pattern.compile("[\\s]+|[.]+|[:]+");
    String interimSanitizedStr = DOT_OR_WHITESPACE_OR_COLON.matcher(namespace).replaceAll("_");
    Pattern FORWARD_SLASH = Pattern.compile("[/]+");
    return FORWARD_SLASH.matcher(interimSanitizedStr).replaceAll(".");
}
```

And it seems to work as expected, which is - replacing ':' with '_' (e.g `127.0.0.1:8081` with `127_0_0_1_8081`) and '/' with '.' (e.g `segment/count` with `segment.count`).
Before I continue working in that direction: @b-slim, @himanshug - you were both involved in adding #1978. Does the above change makes sense to you?

Thanks!
